items.name: Wraith Apex Legends
items.description:
If you want to support me, check out my Patreon for exclusive content and commissions: https://www.patreon.com/Eminic

LoRA model for the character Wraith from Apex Legends. Trained for 10 epochs.

LoRA weight can be anywhere from 0.1-1. It should work fine at 1.

CFG scale 6-8, although you can try experimenting.

Trigger word (optional): "Wraith"

This LoRA is very NSFW friendly, but it can do SFW images just fine as well.

How to use LoRA's in automatic1111's web-ui:

  • Update webui (use git pullor redownload it)

  • Copy the file to stable-diffusion-webui/models/lora

  • Select your LoRA like in this video

  • Make sure to select your desired weight, or leave it at the default of 1. (example: <lora:Wraith:1> is 1 weight, <lora:Wraith:0.5> is 0.5 weight)

If you like this LoRA, I would appreciate a heart as thanks :)

items.name: Baalbuddy Style
items.description:
A clean style with distinct thick lines for your memelord needs.

How to use
While no trigger word is required "greyscale" and/or "monochrome" will produce results closest to the source material.

V1.1 is trained on AOM2 and recommended weight is anything from 0.5 to 1.0 depending on what you prompt and if you're using to prompt in style or as a support LoRA for the linework.

For further prompt tips please see the sample images or the uploaded zip of training tags. As usual all images are raw, slightly cherrypicked, txt2img gens, no inpainting or helper embeddings used.

MISC
Trained on AOM2 at 512 resolution with a dataset of 74 images.
The training was done on a small subset of the artists images, as such the output of this LoRA is not an accurate representation neither in quality or style of the source material. Go support the artist BAALBUDDY if you want the good stuff.

items.name: NBDY Celeste
items.description:
Celeste is the third in my NBDY series for anyone who wants a consistent character for their renders.

Celeste is a Nobody, her unique look is a reflection of their individuality and originality, rather than an attempt to mimic someone else. The character's physical traits combined to create a look that is entirely their own, with no clear inspiration from any one person.

Celeste has a fair complexion, a somewhat rounded face, and straight hair that seems to vary wildly - often times ranging from purple, to white with pink hues, blonde, and black - but will gladly wear it in many colors and styles.

To use this embedding with the Automatic1111 web UI, save the downloaded file to /embeddings/nbdy-celeste-sd15.pt, and then include the trigger word nbdy-celeste-sd15 in your prompt.

Inspired by Zovya's Nobody series. Be sure to check out other contributions to the Nobody tag.

If you like my work, please consider buying me a coffee to show your appreciation.

items.name: BW_GeoAbstract
items.description:
Experimental Lora I made with a dataset of simple black and white geometric shapes I made using Photoshop.

0.1 - .9: Generally has subtle influences on the outcome, making the image lean towards a more simple background, richer colors, and SFW images.

-1 - -.1: Does the opposite, making more complex backgrounds, and subdued colors, and pushes for a more NSFW image despite not having explicit tags in the prompt.

1.1 - 2: Cuases the outcome to be more abstract, making geometric shapes very visible, sometimes even causing the character to disappear. Use with caution.

Trigger word: BW
Monochrome and Greyscale also are stronger. Try giving them negative weights for vivid colors, for example: (monochrome, greyscale:-.3),

Some models react to this lora more than others, best to experiment and see what makes the most interesting thing to you.

If you like this one, you might also like my other Lora that is similar in concept here: https://civitai.com/models/44924/bwheartabstract

items.name: Helga Grey (Goldie Baby)
items.description:
🌟Helga Grey🌟

📢(Helga Grey v1.1 now available) 📢

also known as Goldie Baby, is a Ukrainian-born adult film actress who gained popularity for her stunning looks and alluring performances. She made a name for herself in the industry with a few films released between 2015 and 2016, using various stage names such as Goldie, Goldie B., and Ms. White-Kitten. Known for her piercing blue eyes and natural 5'1" figure, Helga's beauty is complemented by her blonde hair and a 34-inch butt. Her real name is Karen G., and she was born on September 26, 1994, in Kiev, Ukraine. Despite her brief stint in the adult film industry, Helga remains a private person, and little is known about her personal life.

💡Generation Advice💡

🔧Prompt and Sampling (Using auto1111 or similar UX) 🔧

  • Most images have been generated with LORA weighted between 0.65 to 0.75.

  • Lower weighting needed often for headshots.

  • Samples done with CyberRealistic v20 with sampling steps above 20, generally ~40 using Euler a, and DPM++ SDE Karras.

  • When testing a prompt, I often do a low lowres gen of multiple images, then choose the seed I like and upscale.

🚀Upscaling🚀

  • Portrait and close-ups work great using Hires. fix and 8X NMKD-Faces at 0.15 denoise strength.

  • Sometimes I just send it to Ultimate SD upscale after a quick render and run 2x at a scale of two, but often just the Hires. fix is good enough to capture enough details for the subject matter.

  • Ultimate SD upscale script used @ ~.15 - .4 denoising using 8x NMKD Faces or 4X UltraSharp redraw upscalers.

🗒️Side Notes🗒️

  • In contrast to v1.0 and going forward, this LORA should be more ready to produce subject matter details during txt2img. Change your workflow accordingly.

  • The prompts continue to evolve. CyberRealistic is a greatly flexible model for being realism focused and still capturing abstract concepts. I still think they have trumped the SD 1.5 game. 👑

  • Feedback appreciated. Please leave a review if you've used this LORA. 👍

  • Leave a comment if you are having issues getting good output, I'll try to respond.

🏗Change Log🏗

1.1

  • Slightly expanded dataset, added far more detail to face.

  • Changed to new LORA single epoch creation methodology to get more consistent results and settings mostly usable across LORAs.

  • Only tested with Cyberrealistic v2.0, results may vary.

1.0

  • First gen, an incredibly ridiculous amount of steps. Can produce impressive results...sometimes, with way too much fiddling to get it. My first LORA attempt so not surprised.

  • Old release description: Ukrainian model for all you men (and women) of culture. This is my first LORA ever so please understand it is probably not ideal, but I think it is good enough to share. She is one of my favourites, so I'm sure I'll upgrade her in due time.

items.name: Wilykit (Thundercats 2011)
items.description:
Wilykit - Thundercats 2011

This is a Lora based off of (you guessed it), Wilykit from the Thundercats 2011 reboot. This is my first character Lora, so I figured I'd start off with something obscure without a lot of source material to go off of. Great plan, I know.

Works just fine at 0.8 strength.

There are a few quirks with the Lora.

  • Clothing likes to stay pretty close to her color theme and needs some weights added to the color if you want to change it and a negative of what it's generating.

  • Styles also tend to vary from seed to seed, mostly from style bleed from the source images. It's a mix of fan art and official art, so sometimes those can show themselves a bit.

  • The tail showing up is luck of the draw if unprompted. If that's important to you, add it somewhere into the prompt to make it show up a bit better.

  • The face markings and countershading are a similar deal. Luck of the draw. Prompting for "facial mark" might help it to show up better, but maybe not.

I trained it using the Anylora model, and it seems to work fine in different models, but if people are into this Lora, I might retrain it using NAI instead. As I'll be using that as the base to train from now on.

As with my other Lora, it's created using a merge of 2 separately trained Lora. One on the face and one on the body.

modelVersions.description:
v2b is the preferred release model. If you're going to download one of them, this is the one to pick.

It's a 0.6:0.4 ratio merge between the Body (0.6) and Face (0.4) Lora.

Same as the v2b model, but this is a 0.7:0.3 merge of the Body (0.7) and Face (0.3) Lora.

PokespeRed, jacket, red jacket, modern jacket, shirt, black shirt, cap, red cap, forwards cap, wristbands, black wristbands, jeans, blue jeans, black sneakers
